BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw (DDP/ADN) -- Rudolf Scharping, Social 
Democratic Party [SPD] chairman and prime minister of 
Rhineland-Palatinate, continued his talks in Warsaw on 
Wednesday. In the morning he met with Poland's Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak. They discussed how Poland could be brought 
closer to the European Union and to Western defense structures. 
Scharping assured Pawlak of the support of Germany's social 
democrats in the gradual implementation of this intention. 
  Talks are also planned for today with President Lech Walesa 
and Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski, at whose invitation 
Scharping is in Warsaw. 

